2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper focuses on processing and analyzing multimedia data, specifically videos. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new neural network architecture for video classification, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with aggregating frame-level features into a compact feature vector, which is a common task in information retrieval. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper may also fall under this category as it deals with processing and analyzing language in the context of video classification.
